Package com.googlecode.cqengine.index.navigable

Class NavigableIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.support.AbstractAttributeIndex<A,​O>
      • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.support.AbstractMapBasedAttributeIndex<A,​O,​ConcurrentNavigableMap<A,​StoredResultSet<O>>>
        • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.navigable.NavigableIndex<A,​O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModificationListener<O>, AttributeIndex<A,​O>, Index<O>, OnHeapTypeIndex, KeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,​O>, KeyStatisticsIndex<A,​O>, SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,​O>, SortedKeyStatisticsIndex<A,​O>
    public class NavigableIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>
extends AbstractMapBasedAttributeIndex<A,​O,​ConcurrentNavigableMap<A,​StoredResultSet<O>>>
implements SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,​O>, OnHeapTypeIndex
    An index backed by a ConcurrentSkipListMap.

    Supports query types:

    • Equal
    • LessThan
    • GreaterThan
    • Between
The constructor of this index accepts Factory objects, from which it will create the map and value sets it uses internally. This allows the application to "tune" the construction parameters of these maps/sets, by supplying custom factories. For default settings, supply NavigableIndex.DefaultIndexMapFactory and NavigableIndex.DefaultValueSetFactory.
Author:
Niall Gallagher

        public Index<O> getEffectiveIndex()
        Description copied from interface: Index
        Returns the effective index, which Persistence objects will use to determine the identity of the index making persistence requests. Most Index implementations will typically return a reference to themselves ('this'). However in advanced cases when one index delegates to another, the implementation of the wrapping index will create a subclass the delegate index, and override this method in the delegate index so that when the delegate index interacts with the persistence, it will identify itself as the outer or "effective" index.

      • addFilteringForQuantization

        protected Iterable<ResultSet<O>> addFilteringForQuantization​(Iterable<ResultSet<O>> resultSets,
                                                             NavigableIndex.IndexRangeLookupFunction<O> lookupFunction,
                                                             QueryOptions queryOptions)
        A no-op method which may be overridden by subclasses which use a Quantizer.

        This default implementation simply returns the given attribute value unmodified.

        Returns an Iterable which is similar to the one supplied, but which transparently wraps the first ResultSet and/or the last ResultSet returned by the supplied Iterable in a QuantizedResultSet.

        A QuantizedResultSet transparently filters objects in the wrapped ResultSet to ensure that they match the given Query. This is necessary when the index uses a Quantizer, where objects having several adjacent attribute values will be stored together in the same StoredResultSet in the index.

        For range queries (LessThan, GreaterThan, Between), the StoredResultSets in an index using a quantizer at the keys in the index referenced by the query, are not guaranteed to only contain objects matching the values in the query, due to objects being mixed with their adjacent counterparts. Therefore it is necessary to filter the ResultSet at either end of the range.

        Parameters:
        resultSets - ResultSets stored in the index which were found to match the range query, in ascending order of their associated keys
        lookupFunction - Contains parameters specifying whether the first or last ResultSets should be wrapped in a QuantizedResultSet, and also encapsulates the Query against which objects should be filtered
        queryOptions - Optional parameters for the query
        Returns:
        An Iterable optionally with the first and/or last ResultSets wrapped in QuantizedResultSets

      • filterForQuantization

        protected ResultSet<O> filterForQuantization​(ResultSet<O> storedResultSet,
                                             Query<O> query,
                                             QueryOptions queryOptions)
        A no-op method which can be overridden by a subclass to return a ResultSet which filters objects from the given ResultSet, to return only those objects matching the query, for the case that the index is using a Quantizer.

        This default implementation simply returns the given ResultSet unmodified.

        Parameters:
        storedResultSet - A ResultSet stored against a quantized key in the index
        query - The query against which results should be matched
        queryOptions - Optional parameters for the query
        Returns:
        A ResultSet which filters objects from the given ResultSet, to return only those objects matching the query
